   Because much of his work has been funded by fossil-fuel groups,
Balling has been called a rent-a-scientist who's in bed with the
industry. He says none of is work has been compromised and notes
that his largest current grant, $500,000, came from the National
Science Foundation. He disagrees that government-funded research is
