   SWISS-JEWS-NAZIS (Bern, Switzerland) _ Switzerland turned away
thousands of Jewish refugees during World War II despite knowing
they faced death at the hands of the Nazis, a Swiss commission
investigating Swiss wartime policies reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
   U.N.-IRAQ (United Nations) _ The Security Council decided Friday
to extend the U.N. humanitarian program in Iraq for six months
while members pushed toward a vote on a broader resolution to
return U.N. weapons inspectors to Iraq. By Barbara Crossette.
