   PANAMA-ALBRIGHT (Panama City) _ Secretary of State Madeleine
Albright has decided not to attend the canal hand-over ceremony on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   POPE-IRAQ (Rome) _ Dashing Pope John Paul's hopes to visit Iraq
(and the birthplace of Abraham) next year, the Iraqi government
told the Vatican that conditions are not right for a visit. By
Alessandra Stanley.
</P>
<P>
   JAPAN-ROYAL-PREGNANCY (Tokyo) _ After more than six years of a
marriage filled with nervous speculation over whether Crown Prince
Naruhito and his wife, Princess Masako, were able to furnish a
successor to the Chrysanthemum Throne, the Japanese people awoke to
a flood of news reports Friday that the couple would appear to be
bearers of good news. By Howard W. French.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL &LR;  (Moving in ``a'' news file.)
