   RUSSIA-CHECHNYA (Pervomaiskoye, Russia) _ After more than two
months of thunderous bombardments, a small trickle of desperate
residents straggled Friday through the Russian military checkpoint
here. But for Khasan Dakayev, 25, the corridor is more like a
gantlet. He spent weeks worrying that his family might be shot by
Russian soldiers if they left, only to find that the greatest
danger came from gangs of marauders who cruise around Grozny and
its outskirts, brandishing automatic weapons and stealing food with
impunity. By Michael R. Gordon.
