<P>
   PROS
</P>
<P>
   FBN-REEVES-AIDE _ The 79-year-old Marvin Bass is listed in the
Falcons media guide as head coach Dan Reeves' ``special''
assistant. In fact, he has been that since the 1950s, when he
coached the young Reeves at the University of South Carolina. It
began a relationship that would last a lifetime. Bass, who also
coached in the WFL, spent 10 years with Reeves in Denver, then
returned home to South Carolina to ``play out the string.'' He was
floundering three years ago, when Reeves asked him to come work
with the Falcons in Suwanee. So each football season, Bass moves
into the Suwanee Inn and follows Reeves around the Falcons training
facility, charting plays and doing odd jobs. And both men are
better off because of it. (Winkeljohn, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 25. MOVED
</P>
