   COLLEGES
</P>
<P>
   HAMILTON _ ATLANTA _ Will Joe Hamilton become the first player
in Georgia Tech history to win the Heisman Trophy? It's not likely,
but Hamilton will attend the Heisman ceremony tonight in New York.
This has been a busy week for Hamilton. After finishing final
exams, he has traveled from Texas to Florida participating in
college football award ceremonies. (Barnhart, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   w/ALVIN-HAMILTON _ ALVIN, S.C. _The tiny town of Alvin, S.C. is
gearing for a big night on Saturday. The town's favorite son,
Georgia Tech quarterback Joe Hamilton, will be in New York to
participate in the Heisman Trophy awards ceremony. Meanwhile,
family and friends will gather in Alvin hoping to watch Hamilton
win college football's top honor. What are the thoughts of the
people in Alvin heading into the big day? (Clemons, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
