to help glean local orchards and farms for area food banks and
assist in Habitat for Humanity and Union Gospel Mission projects.
Yet there she was on Nov. 30, standing at Pike Street and Third
Avenue in downtown Seattle, when the black-hooded anarchists
arrived to disrupt what had been peaceful civil disobedience
against the World Trade Organization conference. By J.R. LABBE.
