   RUSSIA-CHECHNYA _ MOSCOW _ With a deadline looming for civilians
living in the Chechen capital of Grozny to evacuate the city or
face bombing, the Russian government is showing signs of buckling
under international pressure led by the United States. Developing.
(Holmes, Cox News Service)
</P>
<P>
   MEXICO-VIRGIN _ MEXICO CITY _ Mexicans' firm Catholic faith is
taking a beating just as they gear up to celebrate their national
patron saint, the Virgin of Guadalupe, on Dec. 12. The country is
in an uproar over a letter signed this month by three priests who
have objected to making Juan Diego, a 16th century Aztec Indian, a
saint. Adding insult to injury is the fact that one priest served
in the Virgin's basilica here in the past and another is currently
posted there. The priests say that Diego - who is said to have seen
an apparition of a brown-skinned Virgin in the 1500s _ probably
didn't exist. Those are fighting words to Mexicans of varying
degrees of faith who unite in their reverence for Mexico's Virgin
of Guadalupe. (Ferriss, Cox News Service). WITH PHOTO.
</P>
