<HEADLINE>
NEW YEAR'S EVE ON THE NATION'S MALL 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (For release Sunday, Dec. 12)   (With: MILLENNIUM-CLINTONS.)  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 c.1999 Hearst Newspapers  
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ Here is a list of scheduled New Year's Eve
activities on the National Mall, according to America's Millennium,
the organization coordinating the celebration for the White House:
</P>
<P>
   7:00 p.m.: Black-tie dinner begins at the White House. The
``Creators Dinner'' will honor some of the country's most prominent
figures in sports and the arts and sciences, including playwrights
Arthur Miller and Neil Simon, and Olympian Carl Lewis.
</P>
<P>
   9:30 p.m.: President and Mrs. Clinton and their guests travel to
the Lincoln Memorial, joining a Mall crowd that is expected to
reach 250,000.
</P>
<P>
   10:00 p.m.: The three-hour, nationally televised show,
``Midnight Moment,'' begins. Hosted by actor and rapper Will Smith,
the show includes actors Robert Duvall and Diane Keaton, as well as
opera singers Jessye Norman and Kathleen Battle, gospel singer Bebe
Winans, and 25 New York cast members of the musical hit ``Stomp.''
</P>
<P>
   11:30 to 11:59 p.m.: A live 100-piece orchestra, along with the
combined bands, choirs and marching units of the Armed Forces,
perform a score by award-winning composer John Williams. The music
will accompany an 18-minute movie on America in the 20th century by
academy award-winning director Steven Spielberg.
</P>
<P>
   Following the film, poet laureate Robert Pinsky, his predecessor
Rita Dove and poet-writer Maya Angelou read new works as the music
continues.
</P>
<P>
   Midnight: A spectacular high-tech sound and light show takes
place between the Lincoln Memorial and the Washington Monument as
fireworks light up the sky.
</P>
<P>
   1:00 a.m.: A group of children join the stars of the gala for a
sing-along.
</P>
</TEXT>
