<SLUG> BC-TREESTANDS-$ADV12-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
STAND PUTS NEW SPIN ON HOLIDAY TREE SETUP 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (For release Sunday, Dec. 12)   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By FRANCES INGRAHAM HEINS  
 c.1999 Albany Times Union  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Each year many of us find the perfect Christmas tree, and then
it's time to wrestle it into a tree stand.
</P>
<P>
   If you are still skinning your knuckles and swearing at the
stand you have had for years, convert it into a bird bath and buy a
new one.
</P>
<P>
   Tree stands have come a long way from a cross of wood nailed to
the base of the tree. Now on the market is the patented Swivel
Straight tree stand by Country Line Limited of Solon, Ohio.
</P>
<P>
   Simply by stepping on a pedal, you can swivel the tree into
place. To keep the tree in position, just release the pedal. No
more crawling around on the floor readjusting screws.
</P>
<P>
   County Line's tree stand holds plenty of water (3 1/2- or
5-quart reservoir), is durable, easy to use and comes with a
lifetime guarantee.
</P>
<P>
   Attach the receptacle to the tree trunk and tighten the large
bolts, which have comfortable handles, to make tightening screws
easy. Put the receptacle into the base, depress the foot pedal to
straighten your tree. The pivoting base allows you to swivel the
</P>
<P>
   tree in any direction and the retracting pedal locks it in place
to securely hold the tree in its vertical position.
</P>
<P>
   The large-diameter base distributes weight to support taller
trees. It is made of impact-grade polymer construction that won't
crack, rust or harm floors.
</P>
<P>
   Swivel Straight tree stands are sold in department stores,
hardware stores, mail-order catalogs and garden centers. There are
three models: The largest is for trees of up to 12 feet tall and a
5 3/4-inch diameter trunk. It retails for approximately $69.95. A
stand to fit a 10-foot-tall tree with up to a 5-inch diameter trunk
is $49.95.
</P>
<P>
   Country Line Limited also makes a model for $39.95 with screw
bolts.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-12-10-99 1901EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
