<HEADLINE>
NO BOMB, MALFUNCTION ABOARD EGYPTAIR 990, US OFFICIAL SAYS 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (a and i coding)   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MATTHEW BRELIS  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   A detailed analysis of the cockpit voice recorder of EgyptAir
Flight 990 has uncovered nothing to indicate that a bomb or any
mechanical problem caused the Cairo-bound jet to crash, the
nation's top aviation-safety official said Friday.
