</P>
<P>
   .
</P>
<P>
   ADAIR-INNOCENCE (Los Angeles) -- In an unusual move, a judge has
declared Jeanie Adair factually innocent of the November 1996
beating death of her husband in their Sylmar condominium. The judge
said he found Jeanie Adair had no possible motive to kill Paul
Adair, although she has collected about $400,000 in insurance
money. Adair was not in the courtroom, but said through her
attorney: ``This is the second-best Christmas gift.'' The ruling
will allow Adair to say that she has never been arrested. It will
also clear her record of any mention of the arrest or trial. By
Jesse Hiestand (Will move on the ``n'' California and ``a''
national news wires.)
</P>
<P>
   UNITED-AIRLINES (Los Angeles) _ United Airlines, the No. 1
passenger carrier at Los Angeles International Airport, won City
Council approval Friday for a lease for a new $30-million cargo
facility. The airline has been seeking the lease for the building
without a full environmental review of its impact. United says the
new cargo facility is sorely needed because the existing building
is outdated and inefficient. By Beth Barrett (Will move on the
``n'' California and ``a'' national news wires.)
</P>
<P>
   X X X
</P>
