<SLUG> BC-CARS-GLANCE-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
AT A GLANCE: 2000 HUMMER FOUR-DOOR SOFT-TOP
</HEADLINE>
 
(EDS: Accompanies CARS-WILLIAMS-COLUMN) (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   THE PACKAGE: Huge, four-door, four-passenger, V-8
turbodiesel-powered, sport-utility truck.
</P>
<P>
   HIGHLIGHTS: Way cool! The civilian version of the military
Humvee is an awesome off-road performer and a credible highway
machine, with lots of power, fairly decent on-road handling and a
ride similar to that of a full-size pickup.
</P>
<P>
   NEGATIVES: Cramped interior space, rather wide for narrow city
streets, unreasonably high price tag.
</P>
<P>
   MAJOR COMPETITORS: None.
</P>
<P>
   EPA FUEL ECONOMY: Not available.
</P>
<P>
   BASE PRICE: $79,065 plus $790 transportation.
</P>
<P>
   PRICE AS TESTED: $89,936, including transportation.
</P>
<P>
   ON THE ROAD RATING: A.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
