   (NYT105) UNDATED -- Dec. 10, 1999 -- RUSSIA-CHECHNYA-5 -- Adam
was rushed by a neighbor to Shali hospital near Grozny after having
being hit by bomb shrapnel in the head while playing in the
courtyard of his home in the village of Avtoury. (Bruno Stevens/The
New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT104) UNDATED -- Dec. 10, 1999 -- RUSSIA-CHECHNYA-4 --Sultan,
21, has been rushed to Shali hospital near Grozny after having been
hit by a mortar shell near Gudermes. He lost his left foot and his
left arm is shattered. His loss of blood and lack of treatment has
left him very nemic. (Bruno Stevens/The New York Times)
