<HEADLINE>
HACKETT TO BRING BACK REMAINING ASSISTANTS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   USC football coach Paul Hackett said he intends to bring back
all of his remaining assistants coaches next season.
</P>
<P>
   ``As far as I'm concerned, we've done what we needed,'' Hackett
said. ``As far as anyone being let go, that's not an issue.''
</P>
<P>
   Hackett fired offensive line coach Steve Greatwood two weeks
ago. Greatwood was replaced by tight ends coach Steve Morton, which
leaves a vacancy at that position.
</P>
<P>
   One candidate for the job could be former USC assistant coach
and Los Angeles Rams player Doug Smith.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's a possibility,'' Hackett said.
</P>
<P>
   Hackett said he will decide by Christmas how to shuffle some
responsibilities among the staff. One of the expected changes is
splitting up special teams duties.
</P>
<P>
   Kickoff Classic update: USC is competing with Virginia Tech and
Oklahoma for the lone remaining spot in the Kickoff Classic
opposite Michigan. If Virginia Tech defeats Florida State next
month in the Sugar Bowl, the Hokies are expected to get the bid.
</P>
<P>
   The Kickoff Classic will not make a decision until January.
</P>
</TEXT>
