<P>
   (NYT3) NEW YORK -- Dec. 10, 1999 -- ADV. FOR SUN., DEC. 12 --
NY-KNIT-FASHIONS-2 -- Catherine Shu, 18, works on her knitting as a
part of a knitting circle at Sarah Lawrence College. The group,
which Miss Shu started and his affectionately called the ``stitch
and bitch club'', is just another sign of the growing popularity of
knitting and knit fashions. (Susan Farley/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT2) NEW YORK -- Dec. 10, 1999 -- ADV. FOR SUN., DEC. 12 --
NY-KNIT-FASHIONS-1 -- At The Yarn Company on Manhattan's upper west
side, Cecilia Sun, a customer who just started knitting, gets some
instruction from store owner, Julie Israel. Stores like this have
done away with outdated patterns. They now stock ones for the
latest fashions, and if they don't have one will write patterns for
you. (Suzanne DeChillo/The New York Times) LITE
</P>
