   (NYT1) STOUGHTON, Mass. -- Dec. 10, 1999 -- REEBOK-STRATEGY-1 --
Carl Yankowski, the CEO of Reebok, shows off one of the Traxtar
sneakers in the company's showroom. The Traxtar, a children's shoe
with a computer chip to help measure athletic performance is a big
gamble, because Reebok may be writing off the huge and important
teenage market to distinguish itself from Nike, the market leader.
(Ed Quinn/The New York Times)
</P>
