<HEADLINE>
VANGUARD TO ADD FOUR DAILY FLIGHTS FROM KCI BEGINNING IN MARCH 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By RANDOLPH HEASTER  
 c. 1999 Kansas City Star  
<TEXT>
<P>
   KANSAS CITY, Mo. -- Vanguard Airlines will add four flights from
Kansas City next March.
</P>
<P>
   The airline will add two departures each to Chicago and Denver
from Kansas City International Airport on March 2.
</P>
<P>
   The additional flights will come as Vanguard adds its 14th
Boeing 737 aircraft to its fleet, the company said Friday.
</P>
<P>
   The flights will give Vanguard seven daily departures to Chicago
and eight to Denver from KCI.
</P>
<P>
   Vanguard, based in Kansas City, currently has 21 flights a day
out of KCI.
</P>
<P>
   Russell Winter, Vanguard's vice president of marketing and
planning, said Vanguard's additional flights in its two focus
cities of Kansas City and Chicago had created more connecting
traffic to Vanguard's eight destinations.
</P>
<P>
   ``These flights enable us to build up our presence in these
markets during next year's peak travel season,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Vanguard said the new plane would allow the carrier to start new
nonstop service between Pittsburgh and Atlanta. The carrier will
offer two round-trip flights daily in those markets next March.
</P>
</TEXT>
